node.text: Please!! Keep a distance of 1.5m to cyclists when passing them by car. Please save lives and WAIT for a moment to check the lanes are free before you pass. We want more people on bikes and we want them to feel SAFE. 🙏🌎💚 #gobybike #safetyfirst #greenworld #cyclists

node.text:
Is it a day to remember or a day to forget? 

Firstly, it‘s one to remember because @eviealicerichards took the win for @trekfactoryracingxc - what a champion! So so happy for you! 😍🤩 #teamgoals 

On my side it was a day to forget - or not? 🤔 the smiles + cheering of the kids at the side of the track made my day! And all the adults too, it was the most amazing experience to feel your energy 🔥❤️ I will always remember you!

It was the first time in my whole life - in 9 seasons of racing Elite world cups since 2013 - that I finished a world cup outside the top 20. That is about 60 races… and of all these I was inside the top 10 about 50 times, even with flat tyres and broken hands. So how bad do I have to feel to finish on P25? Pretty, pretty bad.

So in this regard - yes, a day to forget. What I will remember is that I didn‘t give up and finished the race. And I will remember that I showed up and gave my best when it would have been so easy to find an excuse. Character is not built on the easy days. 👊

#worldcup #racing #lenzerheide #trekteam #stillwinning #teamgoals #bestfans #thankyou 

📸 1, 2, 9, 10 @rossbellphoto / @trekfactoryracingxc 
📸 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8 @kenoderleyn / @buffofficial

node.text:
Yoooo! 💐 The legs showed up to the party today and so did the Swiss fans 😍

What a race…! Started from second row, the rider in front of me missed the pedal and we got tangled up and started the race in dead last position! Have you ever overtaken a whole field during one race? Me neither, until today 😅😅 so much fun to race with so many people cheering, thank you!! Also my parents got to be here which made me extra happy 🥰 and @luca_shaw 🥰🥰 my team did an excellent job today, special thanks to @alvarotrek + @beit_size + @lituvz + @jonrourke for the smiles and extra watts 🥳 missed the last fire power in the finale after my furious chase but super stoked on 3rd place tonight 🥰 bike racing can be so much fun! 🍀🕊🌿 

#worldcup #shorttrack #podium #lenzerheide #supercaliber 

PC @rossbellphoto / @trekfactoryracingxc

node.text:
Race action from @rossbellphoto 💥

Thanks to everyone who supported me at the race and the last couple weeks. It was surely the craziest 4 weeks of my life leading up to this race, trying to handle my training and recovery next to running + rushing from one event to the next tv station while answering emails and phone calls. I would have never thought the hype after the Olympics could be that mad. I was also shocked to learn to what extremes people go on a personal + emotional level to try to get from you what they want. I do care a lot to make everyone happy and I guess that‘s what makes it even harder to say no… but I‘m learning and the curve is steep 🤣📈

I always knew it would be tough to race at my best level when you can‘t even do half of the training you usually do. I was just hoping for some magic to be left in my legs from Tokyo! I guess my crash in training didn‘t exactly help either 😳 so coming away with a 5th place in xcc and 4th place in xco still sucks 🤯 but it made me realize that I care too much about racing to just let my life be taken over by appointments! I love to ride my bike + race my bike, and that‘s the only reason why I became a mountain biker! 

Did you know I grew up without a TV? I still don‘t have one. I couldn‘t care less about TV shows and media stuff. I can’t watch them anyways 😂 Yes, I’m happy to give mountain biking a voice and get more people into cycling. But at the end of the day that is not my responsibility. My day only has 24h and I can do plenty of that when I won’t be racing anymore. For now, I am racing. All I want to do is ride my bike. (and win races🥰⚡️)

So going forward my goal is clear… ride my bike + enjoy it 🥳 #ciaociao #freedom  #flow #fun #bikelove

Today, all schoolchildren in Switzerland will go back to their lessons. However, 473 million girls and boys all over the world have no access to schooling. Together with UNICEF, I demand equal opportunities for all children. Because every child in the world has a right to education!
#BacktoSchool #UNICEF #Education #ForEveryChild @UNICEF_CH

node.text:
P4 today 🏁 at xco world championships.
An absolutely amazing ride saw @eviealicerichards take the big W for @trekfactoryracingxc 😍 world champion!! So so stoked and happy for you Evie, congrats!! 

Now if you ever wondered what bike is the fastest… 😜 both Evie and I will tell you it’s the Trek Supercaliber! 🔥

Huge congrats also to @mona.mitterwallner for winning the U23 race!! World champion, wow!! Guess which bike she was racing 😇
 
#racinglove #superpower #supercaliber #trekbikes #sponsored #stoked
#canyouspotthegoldenvalve #goldenbike #goldenstandard 

Photo by @kenoderleyn @buffofficial

node.text:
#backtobusiness 🤎

P5 in today‘s short track world championships. Congrats to @swisscyclingteam @freisina for taking the win and @trekfactoryracingxc @eviealicerichards for silver!

Feel oh-so-good to finally race again… first time since Tokyo. I missed it!! Race mode feeling is coming back and happy to open the legs up for Saturday 😈

📸 @rossbellphoto / @trekfactoryracingxc
